Installing Node.js (if needed):
1. Check if Node.js is already installed by running: node --version
2. If Node.js is not installed, download and install it from https://nodejs.org/
   - Choose the LTS (Long Term Support) version
   - Follow the installation wizard for your operating system
   - Verify installation by running: node --version and npm --version

Installing Sass using npm:
1. Open your terminal or command prompt
2. Navigate to your project directory
3. Install Sass globally using: npm install -g sass
   - This allows you to use Sass from any directory
4. Alternatively, install Sass locally in your project: npm install sass --save-dev
   - This installs Sass only for the current project
5. Verify installation by running: sass --version
